---
// Privacy policy for the IG Growth Tool (internal Meta app "growth-tool").
// Required by Meta to flip a Meta for Developers app from Development to Live mode.
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>IG Growth Tool — Privacy Policy | HMFIC Marketing</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy policy for the IG Growth Tool, an internal-use application operated by HMFIC Marketing." />
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex,follow" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:opsz,wght@9..40,300;9..40,400;9..40,500;9..40,600;9..40,700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --ink: #1a1a1a;
      --muted: #555;
      --bg: #fafafa;
      --accent: #c8a84b;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      font-family: 'DM Sans', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
      color: var(--ink);
      background: var(--bg);
      line-height: 1.65;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 48px 24px;
    }
    main {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      background: white;
      padding: 48px 56px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 32px;
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin: 36px 0 12px;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .meta {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
      padding-bottom: 24px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
    }
    p, li { font-size: 16px; color: var(--ink); }
    li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
    a { color: var(--accent); }
    .contact {
      margin-top: 40px;
      padding: 20px 24px;
      background: #f5f2e8;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 15px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      body { padding: 24px 12px; }
      main { padding: 32px 24px; }
      h1 { font-size: 26px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <h1>IG Growth Tool — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: April 21, 2026</p>

    <h2>About this tool</h2>
    <p>
      The IG Growth Tool (the "Tool") is an internal-use application operated by
      HMFIC Marketing LLC ("we", "us", "our"). It is not offered to the public
      and is used exclusively to help a small number of authorized Instagram
      account operators analyze their own content performance and audience
      engagement. The Tool connects to Instagram via Meta's official Instagram
      Graph API.
    </p>

    <h2>What data we access</h2>
    <p>When an authorized user connects their Instagram account, the Tool accesses:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Their own Instagram business profile information (username, bio, follower count, media count).</li>
      <li>Their own posts, captions, comments, and engagement metrics (likes, comments, reach, saves).</li>
      <li>Public profile information of other Instagram business/creator accounts queried through Meta's Business Discovery API, used for audience and competitor analysis.</li>
      <li>Hashtag search results returned by Meta's official Graph API endpoints.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The Tool does not access private user messages, the account's password,
      payment information, or any data outside what Meta's official APIs return
      to an authorized Page administrator.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use the data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To generate analysis reports (brand voice, audience composition, content performance) for the authorized account operator.</li>
      <li>To draft engagement suggestions (comment replies, outreach prompts) that the authorized operator chooses whether to post manually within the Instagram app.</li>
      <li>To track trends across weekly and monthly snapshots, so operators can measure progress against their own growth goals.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The Tool never automatically posts, comments, or sends direct messages on
      behalf of the user. All actions visible on Instagram are performed
      manually by the authorized human operator.
    </p>

    <h2>Data storage and retention</h2>
    <p>
      Data accessed through the Instagram Graph API is stored in a private
      database on infrastructure controlled by HMFIC Marketing LLC. Access is
      restricted to the authorized account operator and HMFIC Marketing
      personnel directly operating the Tool. Reports and analysis outputs are
      retained for historical trend comparison and can be deleted at any time
      at the request of the authorized account operator.
    </p>

    <h2>Data sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell, license, trade, or share data accessed through the Tool
      with any third party, except for the following service providers acting
      on our behalf under confidentiality obligations:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Anthropic (Claude API), used to generate text analysis and draft engagement suggestions.</li>
      <li>Hosting providers (Hetzner, Vercel) operating the underlying infrastructure.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Deletion rights</h2>
    <p>
      Any authorized account operator may revoke the Tool's access to their
      Instagram account at any time by:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Removing the app from their Facebook account at <a href="https://www.facebook.com/settings?tab=applications">Facebook Settings → Apps and Websites</a>.</li>
      <li>Contacting us at the email below to request deletion of all stored data associated with their account.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Upon a deletion request, we will remove all records associated with the
      operator's account from our database within 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The Tool is not directed to or available for use by anyone under the age
      of 18. We do not knowingly access data from Instagram accounts belonging
      to minors.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Material changes
      will be communicated to authorized operators before they take effect.
      The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent
      revision.
    </p>

    <div class="contact">
      <strong>Contact</strong><br />
      Privacy questions or deletion requests:<br />
      <a href="mailto:matt@hmficmarketing.com">matt@hmficmarketing.com</a><br />
      HMFIC Marketing LLC
    </div>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
